  <TITLE>sign  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 199</DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="sign"> sign function  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <DESCRIPTION>
    <P><VERB>X=sign(A)</VERB> returns the matrix made
    of the signs of <VERB>A(i,j)</VERB>.For complex <VERB/>, <VERB>sign(A) = A./abs(A)</VERB>.
    function.</P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE>
<![CDATA[
sign(rand(2,3))
sign(1+%i)
 ]]>
  </EXAMPLE>
